    NodeVisitor

    public class TransformModelNodeVisitor
extends CloudFormationVisitor
implements NodeVisitor
    Transforms a models nodes.
    Performs the transformation using the prepared EffectiveModel and the already modified CloudFormationModule.

        public void visit(Apache node)
        Transforms the Apache node by moving the configure and start lifecycle operations to its host.
        Instead of the create lifecycle it installs apache2 on the host. Also the command to put the environment variables from the system to the apache is added to the host.

      • visit

        public void visit(JavaApplication node)
        Transforms the JavaApplication node using AWS Beanstalk.
        A Beanstalk Application, Configuration Template and Environment are created. A SecurityGroup is made and assigned to the OptionSettings as well as the environment variables that should be pushed. OptionSettings are settings that influence the Beanstalk Application.
        Specified by:
